---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About — Lynn Baxter">
  <main class="container about">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <img class="portrait" src="/assets/portrait-sketching.jpg" alt="Lynn Baxter sketching on a tablet from the corner of a grey couch" width="220" height="293" />
    <div class="prose">
      <p class="lead">I build tools for families and test them on mine.</p>
      <p>
        I&rsquo;m Lynn &mdash; designer, and keeper of a loud, mostly happy, thoroughly blended
        household &mdash; three adults, three kids &mdash; in Albany, California. I studied biology, then spent nine years running offices
        and buildings for San Francisco startups &mdash; Slack, then Blend &mdash; and the two
        educations agree: every living system fails in predictable ways, and somebody has to love
        it enough to notice early.
      </p>
      <p>
        So that&rsquo;s the job I gave myself. I design for the people raising kids &mdash; not
        because it&rsquo;s <em>soft</em>, but because it&rsquo;s the hardest systems work
        I&rsquo;ve ever met and it lives in my house: a dozen caregivers who each need a
        different slice of the truth, a household that runs on memory and luck. I build the tools
        I wish existed, test them on my own family, and keep honest notes on what breaks. The
        case studies here are those notes.
      </p>
      <p>
        The rest of me, briefly: a UX retraining at BloomTech and two years of freelance product
        design. A decade of narrating audiobooks &mdash; a children&rsquo;s collection and a
        vampire mystery, because range is a virtue. An abiding love of old words, new tools, and
        soup. And early-childhood-education coursework at Berkeley City College, because the
        families I design for deserve more than my anecdotes.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you&rsquo;re making something kind and serious for families,
        <a class="reach" href="mailto:lynnmariebee@gmail.com">I&rsquo;d love to hear about it</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>

  <style>
    .about { padding-block: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 3rem) clamp(3rem, 8vw, 4rem); max-width: 680px; }
    .portrait { width: 220px; height: auto; border-radius: var(--radius); margin: 1rem 0 2rem; }
    .prose .lead {
      font-family: var(--font-display);
      font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 1.2rem + 1.9vw, 2.1rem);
      font-weight: 500;
      line-height: 1.15;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
      margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    }
    .prose p { font-size: clamp(1.05rem, 1rem + 0.35vw, 1.15rem); line-height: 1.7; margin: 0 0 1.3rem; max-width: 60ch; color: var(--color-ink); }
    .prose em { font-style: italic; color: var(--color-clay); }
    .reach { color: var(--color-clay); text-decoration-thickness: 1px; text-underline-offset: 3px; }
    .reach:hover { text-decoration-thickness: 2px; }
  </style>
</Base>
